"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-arts-entertainment-tv-news-tom-cruise-olympics-stunt-mission-impossible-b2594913.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Some fans considered the stunt too 'predictable'  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Tom Cruise's dramatic stunt at theOlympic closing ceremony in Parishas received a mixed reaction from viewers.\", \"from\": 348, \"to\": 482, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 372, \"end\": 382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To mark the handover from Paris toLos Angeles- where the 2028 games will be hosted - theMission: Impossibleactordramatically abseiled off the Stade de France roof, landed in a crowd of fans before hopping on a motorbike and riding out of the stadium while holding the Olympic flag.\", \"from\": 484, \"to\": 765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 510, \"end\": 515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.269659815900337e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 626, \"end\": 641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 626, \"end\": 641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A pre-recorded film then showed the actor, who is known for performing all of his own stunts, travelling through Paris and driving onto a plane, before he eventually parachuted down to the ground, landing at the Hollywood sign in Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 1009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 880, \"end\": 885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.269659815900337e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 979, \"end\": 993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\"}, {\"begin\": 997, \"end\": 1008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.690723110766101e-16, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere at the closing ceremony, American musicians Billie Eilish and H.E.R performed to showcase Californian talent, while \\\"Can not Stop\\\" by the LA band Red Hot Chili Peppers was played during Cruise's Mission: Impossible moment.\", \"from\": 1011, \"to\": 1243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1046, \"end\": 1054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.662430723064135, \"rank\": 0.2889562710762937, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1065, \"end\": 1078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Billie Eilish\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\"}, {\"begin\": 1167, \"end\": 1188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Red Hot Chili Peppers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cruise's appearance had already been predicted by some fans, since he was spotted several times in Paris in the past fortnight while cheering on the US team in the swimming relay and watching multi-medal-winning American gymnast Simone Biles in action.\", \"from\": 1245, \"to\": 1497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1344, \"end\": 1349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.269659815900337e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1394, \"end\": 1396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"score\": 0.6227063934071215, \"rank\": 0.4852315979440416, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\"}, {\"begin\": 1457, \"end\": 1465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.662430723064135, \"rank\": 0.2889562710762937, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1474, \"end\": 1486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On social media, some fans suggested that the stunt was a little too predictable.\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1580, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Happy Olympics Closing Ceremony or as it's better known Tom Cruise Is Gonna Do a Crazy Stunt Day,\\\" wrote one viewer on X/Twitter, as another called the stunt \\\"totally unsurprising,\\\" adding: \\\"I can imagine Tom Cruise doing [something] like this on a casual Tuesday\\\".\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1639, \"end\": 1649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}, {\"begin\": 1788, \"end\": 1798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Others marvelled at theMission: Impossible-style stunt, with one viewer writing: \\\"[Cruise] did all of his favourite stunts, jumped off of a building, rode a motorcycle, ran a bit, climbed a bit, and of course jumped out of an aeroplane.\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 2086, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A Mission Impossible supercut.\\\"\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2118, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An American viewer remarked that it set the tone for the spectacle that will be the LA games, predicting it will be \\\"obnoxious all over the place\\\".\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2123, \"end\": 2131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.662430723064135, \"rank\": 0.2889562710762937, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Others noticed the difference between the artistic decisions from the French side versus the US side, with one X/Twitter user joking: \\\"France: 'This was nice let us do some art and some weird stuff to close the show and it'll be nice'.\", \"from\": 2269, \"to\": 2504, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2339, \"end\": 2345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9982117477399681, \"rank\": 0.0008962594368300502, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2362, \"end\": 2364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"score\": 0.6227063934071215, \"rank\": 0.4852315979440416, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\"}, {\"begin\": 2404, \"end\": 2410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9981768041427436, \"rank\": 0.0009581187798719025, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Watch Apple TV+ free for 7 day  New subscribers only.\", \"from\": 2506, \"to\": 2559, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a39.99/mo.\", \"from\": 2560, \"to\": 2569, \"entities\": []}, {